            <p><em>*Yields are indicative as of April 2026 and change with each auction. T-Bills are issued at a discount to face value.</em></p>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Benefits</span>
              <h2>Why Invest in Government Bonds?</h2>
            </div>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Zero Credit Risk</strong><p>Government bonds carry sovereign guarantee — the highest possible credit quality. There has never been a default on Indian government securities, making them the safest investment instrument available in the country.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>RBI Retail Direct Access</strong><p>Retail investors can now open a free account on the RBI Retail Direct portal and participate in primary auctions alongside institutional investors. This eliminates broker fees and provides direct access to government securities.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>High Liquidity</strong><p>G-Secs are the most liquid fixed-income instruments in India with active daily trading on NDS-OM platform and stock exchanges. You can buy or sell at any time during market hours at transparent market prices.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Excellent Collateral Value</strong><p>Government bonds are accepted as premium collateral by banks, clearing corporations, and exchanges. They can be pledged to obtain loans at very competitive interest rates, enhancing their utility beyond just returns.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Portfolio Stabilizer</strong><p>During equity market downturns, government bonds typically appreciate as investors move to safety. This negative correlation makes them an essential component for reducing portfolio volatility and protecting wealth during crises.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Flexible Tenure Options</strong><p>From 91-day Treasury Bills for short-term parking to 40-year bonds for long-term wealth preservation, G-Secs offer unmatched flexibility in tenure selection to match any investment horizon or liability.</p></div></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">How to Invest</span>
              <h2>How to Buy Government Bonds</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="steps-grid">
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">1</div><h3>Open RBI Retail Direct</h3><p>Register on the RBI Retail Direct portal with your PAN, Aadhaar, and bank details. The account is free and opens a gilt account directly with RBI.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">2</div><h3>Choose Security Type</h3><p>Select between Treasury Bills (short-term), dated G-Secs (medium to long-term), or floating rate bonds based on your investment horizon and income needs.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">3</div><h3>Bid in Auction</h3><p>Place non-competitive bids in RBI auctions for allotment at the weighted average price. Or buy from the secondary market through stock exchanges at prevailing market prices.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">4</div><h3>Receive Interest & Maturity</h3><p>Interest is credited to your linked bank account semi-annually. On maturity, the face value is automatically redeemed and credited back to your account.</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>

